#### Quick Guide to use SpikingNeuronModel ####

Four files:
- DIV25_PREmethod.npy : coupling strength matrix in Numpy .npy binary file format
- SpikingNeuronModel.py : library for conductance-based spiking neuron model
- Example-1.py : example run of model from scratch for 40 time steps (illustrating the framework of a simulation run)
- Example-2.py : example run of model continuing from 40 time steps till 100 time steps (illustrating the loadFromPrev argument)

After running Example-1.py, two folders appear, namely 'out-plot/' and 'out-cont/'
- 'out-plot/' : to store raster & time series plots
- 'out-cont/' : to store necessary continuation files (model params & network states) for future runs

Python libraries required:
- tqdm
- numpy
- matplotlib

To run the examples, in the terminal, do:
1. python Example-1.py
2. python Example-2.py
